<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>WeatherBeacon</title>
  <%= stylesheet_link_tag    "application", :media => "all" %>
  <%= javascript_include_tag "application" %>
  <%= csrf_meta_tags %>
</head>
<body>
<div class="navbar navbar-inverse navbar-fixed-top">
      <div class="navbar-inner">
        <div class="container">
          <a class="btn btn-navbar" data-toggle="collapse" data-target=".nav-collapse">
            <span class="icon-bar"></span>
            <span class="icon-bar"></span>
            <span class="icon-bar"></span>
          </a>
          <a class="brand" href="/">Weather Beacon</a>
          <div class="nav-collapse collapse">
            <ul class="nav">
              <li class="active"><a href="/">Home</a></li>
              <li><%= link_to "About", '#'  %></li>
            </ul>
          </div><!--/.nav-collapse -->
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
<a href="#myModal" role="button" class="btn btn-success" data-toggle="modal">What Do the Colors Mean?</a>
<%= yield %>
<div class="modal hide fade" id="myModal">
  <div class="modal-header">
    <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">&times;</button>
    <h3 style="color: black;">What Do the Colors Mean?</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="modal-body">
    <p>To Explain the colors here is a rhyeme:</p>
    <p>"Weather Beacon <span style='color: red;'>red</span>, warmer weather ahead.</p>
    <p>Weather Beacon white, colder weather in sight.</p>
    <p>Weather Beacon <span style='color:green;'>green</span>, no change in temperature foreseen.</p>
    <p>Weather Beacon flashing night or day, precipitation is on the way"</p>
    <p></p>
    <p>Thanks to KCCI, Des Moines, for the rhyme.</p>
    <p>Weather Infomation is provided by: <%= link_to "wunderground.com", "http://www.wunderground.com" %></p>
  </div>
  <div class="modal-footer">
    <a href="#" class="btn">Close</a>
  </div>
</div>
</body>
